description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for 1 suitably experienced Podiatrists to join the Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust Acute Podiatry Service at the Royal Free Hospital sites as a Band 7 Advanced Specialist Podiatrist. You will be working alongside a group of Podiatrists as part of a multidisciplinary team in both inpatient and outpatient settings mainly based at Barnet &amp; Chase Farm Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be clinicians who can provide highly specialised care. You may be expected to be able to provide assessment and treatment for patients presenting with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute foot pathology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diabetic patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Musculoskeletal conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rheumatology conditions,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wound care management needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will take a lead role in the advanced assessment, diagnosis and treatment of patients who have complex pathology. They should be able to provide advanced wound care for patients at risk of amputation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will play a significant role in the delivery of a multidisciplinary, patient focused service through evidence based protocols/pathways facilitating holistic patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work as part of a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Free London NHS Trust has three main hospital sites- Royal Free Hampstead, Barnet Hospital and Chase Farm Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Julian Livingstone&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Consultant Podiatrist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: (020) 8216-4373&lt;/p&gt;
